7 Sec. 229. Revenues that remain in the settlements fund at the
8 end of the fiscal year carry forward into the succeeding fiscal
9 year.
10 Sec. 230. (1) In addition to any other requirements under this
11 part, if the department is authorized under this part to expend
12 funds in addition to those appropriated in part 1, the department
13 must do all of the following:
14 (a) Not later than November 1, provide a report to the
15 chairpersons of the house and senate appropriations committees, the
16 house and senate fiscal agencies, and the state budget office that
17 details all of the following:
18 (i) The type of funding received during the previous fiscal
19 year that was authorized in part 2 of the article that made
20 appropriations for the department in the previous fiscal year.
21 (ii) When the funding was received.
22 (iii) The amount of funding received.
23 (iv) How much of the funding was spent and for what purpose or
24 purposes.
25 (b) Not later than 60 days after receipt of funds authorized
26 under this part, provide a report to the chairpersons of the house
27 and senate appropriations committees, the house and senate fiscal
28 agencies, and the state budget office that details all of the
29 following:
RMH S06106'26 (S-1) n52eu9

26
1 (i) The type of funding received.
2 (ii) When the funding was received.
3 (iii) The amount of funding received.
4 (iv) The anticipated or actual amount to be spent and the
5 specified purpose or purposes.
6 (c) Not later than February 15, provide a report to the
7 chairpersons of the house and senate appropriations committees, the
8 house and senate fiscal agencies, and the state budget office with
9 an estimate of funding authorized by this part that the department
10 anticipates it will receive in the subsequent fiscal year,
11 identifying all of the following:
12 (i) The type or types of funding anticipated.
13 (ii) The amount or amounts of funding anticipated.
14 (iii) The purpose or purposes of the funding.
15 (2) If another reporting requirement under this part would
16 provide substantially similar information on a substantially
17 similar time frame as would be reported under subsection (1),
18 subsection (1) does not apply.
