7 Sec. 238. The department shall submit a report to the senate
8 and house standing committees and appropriations subcommittees with
9 primary responsibility for issues under the jurisdiction of the
10 department that details departmental activities of the most recent
11 fiscal year in administering permitting programs. The report must
12 include, at a minimum, all of the following:
13 (a) The number of FTEs assigned to each permitting program and
14 the number of unfilled positions at the beginning and end of the
15 most recent fiscal year.
16 (b) The number of permit applications received by the
17 department in the preceding year, including applications for new
18 and increased uses and reissuances.
19 (c) The number of permits for each program approved.
20 (d) The number of permits for each program denied.
21 (e) The percentage and number of permit applications that were
22 reviewed for administrative completeness within statutory time
23 frames.
24 (f) The percentage and number of permit applications for which
25 a final action was taken by the department within statutory time
26 frames for new and increased uses and reissuances.
27 (g) Activities to reduce any backlog of permits that exceed
28 the statutory time frames and the average time frame for permit
29 approvals for each program.
